article.headline: Wofford 94, West Virginia Wesley 60
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Shane Nichols tied his career-high with 28 points, including seven of Wofford's school-record tying 18 3-pointers, as the Terriers beat West Virginia Wesleyan 94-60 on Wednesday night. Wofford (5-9) led 16-7 less than seven minutes into the game, with Nichols scoring 14 of those points. The Terriers led by as many as 44 points in the second half. Wofford shot 50 percent (18-of-36) on 3-pointers, compared to 7.1 percent (1-of-14) shooting behind the arc for the Bobcats (1-8). The Terriers had 10 steals and forced 18 turnovers. Matt Estep added 15 points, all on 3-pointers, while Drew Gibson had 12 points and five rebounds for Wofford. Keshawn Creighton scored 11 points and had seven rebounds, while Chris Smith added 10 points for West Virginia Wesleyan.
